text: The Global Sales field was identified as a string for me for some reason. I couldn't change it to decimal because most of the values turned to NULL when I did it.  My solution: Write "sep=,", without the quotes, on the first row of the csv file; open the csv file using Excel and save it as a Excel Worksheet; now connect to the Excel Worksheet instead of the csv file on Tableau and the all the Sales fields show be identified as decimal values already!

author: @darkwing3825
text: I just started watching your content and I love the work and QUALITY (!!!) that you have put into this work. One suggestion I would make is to be more specific where on the page buttons are when you speak. In this video, you often say "We'll go over here and do X", but as I was trying to follow along, I often lost exactly where on the page you clicked and I had to rewind in order to keep up (I watch videos on one screen and actively follow along on another). This was especially important in software like Tableau, which is mostly just icons. So if you could say something more like "We'll go over to the bottom left of the chart" instead of "over here", I think it could help a lot of people follow along much easier and reinforce what you're saying. Not a huge problem because YouTube is infinitely rewindable, but I figured it could help.

text: I learned a lot thank you. I do have to say that it would be very helpful for those watching the video if you would be more specific with your directions. Following a cursor can be like trying to find the golden snitch, but worse when it is the same color as the screen. Instead of go here, how about go here "to the bottom right", or click this "icon with the down arrow on the top bar", or over here "on the left". Adding those simple directional or descriptive cues will help your audience follow along better, and not have to rewind the video multiple times for each step you are taking.
